'And of those eighty-four thousand cities I dwelt in just one, Kusāvatī,… of the eighty-four thousand wives I had, just one looked after me, and she was called Khattiyāni or Velāmikāni;
of the eighty-four thousand bales of cloth I had just one … ; of the eighty-four thousand rice-offerings there was just one measure of choice curry that I ate.
